mothers of the Palestinian prisoners with blood on their hands, in
the words of the Israelis. Scarves swaddling their heads, the women
sit cross-legged on Muslim prayer rugs inside an army tent in a
public square here, holding framed photographs in their laps. Since
Saturday they have been fasting in solidarity with their sons,
prisoners on hunger strike in Israeli jails. One by one they
wearily offered hair-raising testimonials. By Deborah Sontag.
