most, told him immediately that he had stumbled upon a rare visual
harvest _ a cornucopia of hundreds of ravishing photographs of
fruits, flowers and mundane vegetables, magically transformed into
art by one Charles Jones. But exactly who was this Jones? And when
had he lived? By R.W. Apple Jr.
