<P>
   These columns for release Thursday, December 10, 1998 are moving
today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   MURRAY-COLUMN _ LUFKIN, Texas _ What with my wife out of town, I
stopped by one of the nice family restaurants hereabouts for Sunday
lunch. I arrived just in time to join the church crowd. Just in
time, too, as it turned out, for a sermon. (Murray, Cox News
Service) MOVED TUESDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ The movement has begun, folks.
There was so much response to my column last week suggesting
starting a political action group to get rid of humorless people
that I've decided to actually form GRUMP. Members of Good Riddance
to Unrelentingly Morose People, or GRUMP, will keep a diligent eye
out for grumbly behavior. (Kelso, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ Traveling has always brought me
pleasure. Leaving home without all my stuff has always brought me
anxiety. The only time in my life that I have traveled without
suffering packing remorse was when I was in the military. Then I
was told what to take. No more and no less. But in civilian life
packing for trips involves choices. Way too many choices for me.
(Nethaway, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
