   GREG-HAUPTNER _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Meet Greg Hauptner _ a
former long-haired hippie turned savvy (some might say shameless)
self-promoter. Or, as one friend put it, a man who knows how to get
his name in the papers. And in magazines and on TV. Hauptner, 52,
has been featured in People, Vogue, Family Circle and was even
selected by CBS News as one of the six most successful business
people in Florida in the late '70s. One glance at Hauptner's
extensive four page _ yes four page! _ resume shows he's been a
hairdresser (he once owned a string of shops, but is now stylists
director at Elizabeth Arden in Palm Beach Gardens), author (five
motivational-style books), management seminar leader and even
stuntman in the awful 1992 film Cop and a Half (he fought with Burt
Reynolds during a barroom brawl). Now you can add another
occupation to Hauptner's job-filled resume _ TV host. (Thompson,
Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   JOAN-LUNDEN _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ You'd think, after 20
years on TV, where mere seconds can make or lose millions, Joan
Lunden could answer questions quickly. Not today, my friend.
(Grantham, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
