<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-09 13:01 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0569 &Cx1f; tad-z
u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-VIDEO-PARENTTRAP10-CO     12-09 0186
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-VIDEO-PARENTTRAP10-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Ritzy remake of Disney classic a fantasy worth checking out
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``The Parent Trap'' (PG)
</P>
<P>
   OK, so maybe Baby Boomers won't ever get over the cultural
touchstone of Hayley Mills and Hayley Mills singing ``Let's Get
Together.'' But this affectionate remake of the Freudian fantasy,
with newcomer Lindsay Lohan, will keep kids enthralled. Lohan plays
Hallie and Annie, twin sisters separated as tykes, and unaware of
the others' existence. That is, till they're reunited at a summer
camp for the cell phone set . . . and plot to reunite their
estranged parents by switching places. Adults will dig the sexy
pairing of Dennis Quaid and Natasha Richardson as the parents.
Plus, there's the eye-candy of their conspicuous-consumption
lifestyles: He's a Napa Valley vineyard owner, she's a London haute
couture designer. Like we said, it's a fantasy. Priced to buy,
$22.99. Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   Steve Murray writes for the Atlanta Journal- Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
