<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    New titles sure to please the guys on your list
 &HT;    By Eleanor Ringel
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   20th Century Fox got into the DVD game late, but the company has
launched a small flotilla of ``older'' titles in time for the
holidays. Most are for the boys _ Steven Seagal in ``Marked for
Death,'' Arnold Schwarzenegger in ``Predator,'' the one, the only,
the original ``Porky's.'' For the girls, well, there's ``Hope
Floats.'' It just came out on video, but it looks better on DVD.
And you can watch it with Spanish subtitles if you're in the mood.
</P>
<P>
   A more classic choice for the DVD fan on your list might be
``Gone With the Wind,'' based on the book about Atlanta that Tom
Wolfe didn't write. The soundtrack has been digitally remastered,
the original technicolor tint restored and, thanks to the DVD
format, you can jump directly to your favorite scene.
</P>
<P>
   Eleanor Ringel writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
