<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BEAM-COLUMN-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HOLIDAY BRAGGING RIGHTS _ AND WRONGS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By ALEX BEAM  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
The Joyes 
110 Threadwillow Drive 
Bluefish Cove, MA 
 
Dear Friends, 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   How time seems to fly when there's so little of it left _ I mean
BEFORE THE MILLENNIUM. Da-da-da-da! Are you ready? We sure are! And
what a year we've had getting ready for THE BIG EVENT!
</P>
<P>
   (I'm hoping for one of those big Hollywood comets, or maybe a
nice, quick thermonuclear war to wipe the slate clean so I can free
myself from this den of losers.)
</P>
<P>
   You know how good Jon is with computers. . . . Well, he's
turning that Year 2000 problem you read so much about to his
advantage! That's right! He's become a high-priced Y2K consultant!
</P>
<P>
   (What a scam! For once, I'm envious, and for once we're able to
send the mortgage check out on time. Jon and his crew of jailbait
hackers are like those Animal Control crooks who charge $50 to
remove a skunk from your property, and then dump it in your
neighbor's yard!
</P>
<P>
   Here's how it works: Jon's gang spends a few days lobbing virus
bombs at the Web site of some clueless business. Then Jon shows up
on their doorstep, blows some Y2K smoke in their faces, and bingo!
Sooner than you can say Thomas Penfield Jackson, the bozos hire Jon
for $1,000 a day, plus expenses. And what do you know? After a few
weeks, the ``problem'' mysteriously vanishes. Good work if you can
get it!)
</P>
<P>
   Jon Jr. is back in college, slaving away. The year off in
California gave him some helpful perspective. Now he knows he
doesn't have to rush through school just to get a minimum-wage job
wrapping up bean sprouts in some flaccid tortilla. He's wisely
decided to enhance his skill set before joining the work force.
</P>
<P>
   (Six years at UMass! That's like what? A high school equivalency
degree? That 1.5 GPA is OK for the basketball players, but alas,
the school's not quite as flexible where the Ultimate Frisbee JV is
concerned. Maybe we could get him diagnosed . . .)
</P>
<P>
   How's ``baby'' Johanna? Baby, you should see her now!
Five-foot-two, eyes of blue _ the rest of it is up to you . . . to
imagine. She's taking a break before going off to college, and with
her superb presentation skills, she's already landed a
high-commission sales job!
</P>
<P>
   (What's her street name? Tiffany Amber? Or is that Billy Joel's
daughter? Everybody's a hooker these days. What the heck, she's of
age. I keep my eye glued to the police blotter, waiting for the day
that Hugh Grant picks her up on one of his swings through town. If
the cops call, I'll say I don't know her. Sooner or later these
kids have to leave the nest.)
</P>
<P>
   I know you're curious about my Appalachian cuisine catering
business. Well, I'm sorry to report that ``Deliverance'' is no
more. I had so many customers that I had to make a choice between
becoming the next Martha Kostyra _ sorry, Stewart _ and being a
wife and mother. Luckily, one of my partners was eager to take over
the business.
</P>
<P>
   (Some partner _ those fershlugginer bankers! Believe me, I'll
have Jon's virusniks blowing up their back office systems soon
enough. But every cloud does have a silver lining. Now the IRS, the
INS, the Department of Labor, and the health inspectors are their
problem, not mine.)
</P>
<P>
   But you know me _ I'm no quitter! I've got a business plan that
I hope will be the salvation of us all!
</P>
<P>
   (My new business? Pure gravy! Not too many people noticed the
Pope's recent announcement that the Catholic Church will be
granting indulgences again, to celebrate the Year 2000 Jubilee.
Guess what? I've landed the New England franchise! When my Web site
www.Send$500You'reSaved.com goes up, we'll be millionaires! In your
face, Martin Luther! God bless the Millennium! Hallelujah!)
</P>
<P>
   Got to run! Here's hoping that 1998 has been as fun and
productive for your family as it has been for ours! Happy holidays
and Joye-ous New Year to one and all! Stay in touch!
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
FROM THE JOYES: JOYCE, JONATHAN, JJ AND JOHANNA &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
