<P>
   UNDATED _ When I was in elementary school, my family had a
silver Christmas tree. I loved that tree. It was about 5 feet tall
and no matter where I stood, I could see right through it because
the branches were sparse and so far apart. I don't know what the
tree was made of, but I think it might have been aluminum because
after Christmas we'd stick a couple of the sparkly limbs on top of
the television to improve the reception. By MONICA FRAZIER
ANDERSON. Story will move in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
