Forget about the partisan conflict that seems to dominate American
politics today. Albert Gore Sr. was a politician who transcended
such concerns. When Gore died over the weekend at the age of 90,
Vice President Al Gore lost his father, and our nation lost a
statesman. By BILL THOMPSON. Story will move in ``k'' commentary
caregory. &QL; 
