   NONFICTION
</P>
<P>
   --------------------------------------------------------
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-NANKING-NYTSF, THE GOOD MAN OF NANKING, The Diaries of
John Rabe. Edited by Erwin Wickert. Illustrated. 294 pp. New York:
Alfred A. Knopf. $26. The diaries of a German civilian who saved
thousands during the Rape of Nanking.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-SHERIDAN-1000&AMP;ADD-NYTSF, A TRAITOR'S KISS, The Life of
Richard Brinsley Sheridan, 1751-1816. By Fintan O'Toole. 519 pp.
New York: Farrar, Straus &AMP; Giroux. $30. As an Irishman, Richard
Brinsley Sheridan was doomed to a life in the margins.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-WONDER-NYTSF, SURPASSING WONDER, The Invention of the
Bible and the Talmuds, By Donald Harman Akenson. 658 pp. New York:
Harcourt Brace &AMP; Company. $35. A new study of the origins of
Scripture and how it has changed.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-GIBRAN-1000&AMP;ADD-NYTSF, PROPHET, The Life and Times of
Kahlil Gibran, By Robin Waterfield. Illustrated. 366 pp. New York:
St. Martin's Press. $25.95. KAHLIL GIBRAN, Man and Poet: A New
Biography, By Suheil Bushrui and Joe Jenkins. Illustrated. 372 pp.
Boston: Oneworld Pubs. $28.95. Two new biographies of Kahlil
Gibran, the Lebanese poet and philosopher.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-TROLLOPE-NYTSF, FANNY TROLLOPE, The Life and Adventures
of a Clever Woman. By Pamela Neville-Sington. Illustrated. 416 pp.
New York: Viking. $29.95. ``A vulgar pushing woman'': that was
Robert Browning's description of the fearless Fanny Trollope.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-DANDY-NYTSF, THE COWBOY AND THE DANDY, Crossing Over
From Romanticism to Rock and Roll. By Perry Meisel. Illustrated.
156 pp. New York: Oxford Press. $24.95. According to Perry Meisel,
the English Romantics paved the way for rock-and-roll.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-CAREFULLY-NYTSF, OPEN ME CAREFULLY, Emily Dickinson's
Intimate Letters to Susan Huntington Dickinson. Edited by Ellen
Louise Hart and Martha Nell Smith. 323 pp. Ashfield, Mass.: Paris
Press. Paper, $19.95. Emily Dickinson's letters to her
sister-in-law are short, impassioned and not easy to interpret.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-MOVIES-1000&AMP;ADD-NYTSF, MOVIES AND MONEY, By David
Puttnam with Neil Watson. Illustrated. 337 pp. New York: Alfred A.
Knopf. $27.50. Americans recognized very early that the movies
could become a legitimate industry.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-FRAN-NYTSF, FINDING FRAN, History and Memory in the
Lives of Two Women. By Lois W. Banner. Illustrated. 243 pp. New
York: Columbia Press. $24.95. One teen-age girl grew up to be a
feminist historian; her best friend would embrace Islam.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-LION-NYTSF, IF A LION COULD TALK, Animal Intelligence
and the Evolution of Consciousness, By Stephen Budiansky. 219 pp.
New York: The Free Press. $25. A new study about how much animals
understand.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-JORDAN-NYTSF, BARBARA JORDAN, American Hero, By Mary
Beth Rogers. Illustrated. 414 pp. New York: Bantam Books. $27.50.
