<P>
   COKE-GROWTH _ ATLANTA _ Merrill Lynch analyst Emanuel Goldman
continues to expect below-trend-line volume growth for Coca-Cola
Co. in the fourth quarter, and said the 1999 volume trends appear
problematic because of the difficult global economy. In a research
note Wednesday, he said the company will be hurt by four fewer
shipping days in the fourth quarter. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
