going to make the world a more pleasant place to wake up ``one
morning at a time.'' Herold received U.S. patent No. 5,832,067 for
a ``method and apparatus for integrating telephone signals with an
alarm clock.'' He calls it a ``new clock radio.'' It delivers
predetermined messages when you awake _ more pleasant ones than
commercial radio broadcasts. (Tharpe, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
