<HEADLINE>
DEMAND FOR MODEL T PARTS STILL MOVING
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: I have acquired some old Model T parts from my grandfather's
estate. How can I find out if anyone wants them? _ L.N., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: A place to start is a local chapter of the Model T Ford Club
of America. ``There are lots of people who want Model T parts,''
said Harry Wistrand, president of the group's Dallas chapter.
</P>
<P>
   The Dallas chapter meets the first Sunday of each month at
Central Congregational Church in Dallas. The next gathering is Jan.
3.
</P>
<P>
   The chapter, which has about 125 members and 150 Model Ts, costs
$12 a year to join. Membership in the national club costs an
additional $22 and includes a subscription to its magazine.
</P>
<P>
   For more information, write to Ted Dumas, 13409 Spring Grove
Ave., Dallas 75240.
</P>
<P>
   Q: When I ask people what the saying ``feet of clay'' means,
they all give different answers. What is the meaning and origin of
this expression? _ C.M., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: The term ``feet of clay'' was inspired by Daniel 2:42 in the
Bible. King Nebuchadnezzar has a dream about a statue made of
several materials, including toes of iron and clay, ``so the
kingdom shall be partly strong, and partly broken.''
</P>
<P>
   Greg Hartman writes that the expression ``is used in reference
to someone who is untrustworthy; someone who might disappear when
the going gets tough.''
</P>
<P>
   Hartman, an editor for Focus on the Family, publishes a
Christian humor Web site at christianhumor.miningco.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Bright-yellow Christmas bulbs in C7 and C9 sizes have not
been available in Fort Worth for several years. Can you tell me
why? _ S.T., Weatherford, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Christmas lights retailer All American Christmas Co. didn't
know why they might not be available.
</P>
<P>
   The company sells C7 bulbs in yellow and C9 bulbs in a
red-yellow (amber) color. The cost is $150 for a case of 1,000 C7
bulbs and $160 for 1,000 C9 bulbs.
</P>
<P>
   ``We may be able to find some C9 bulbs that are yellow,''
company assistant Rhonda Prater said. For more information, call
(888) 726-8235 or visit www.aachristmas.com.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
