   CLINTON-PERJURY (Washington) _ White House witnesses tell the
House Judiciary Committee that President Clinton is being held to a
tougher standard of conduct than an ordinary citizen would be and
therefore should not be impeached. Republican committee members
respond that the president is not an ordinary citizen. By MARK
HELM. (Already filed.)
