<P>
   &UR; NATURAL ELEGANCE: ADD SPARKLE TO YOUR HOLIDAY TABLE WITH FRUIT &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (1,200 words) &QL; 
 &UR; DRESS UP YOUR FRONT DOOR WITH WREATHS AND SWAGS MADE FROM WINTER'S
HARVEST
 &UR; (1,000 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By MARTHA STEWART &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; ADAPTED FROM ``DECORATING FOR THE HOLIDAYS: CHRISTMAS WITH MARTHA
STEWART LIVING, VOLUME 2'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   America's doyenne of better living offers advice on how to
brighten up your home for the holidays. (slugged:
BC-HOLIDAY-DECORATING-MARTHA-STEWART-FRUIT-NYTSF, priority code r,
category code l and
BC-HOLIDAY-DECORATING-MARTHA-STEWART-WREATHS-NYTSF, priority code
r, category code l)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HANUKKAH BUSHES? BAH, HUMBUG! &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (500 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By EVE GLICKSMAN &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   ``There's nothing like Christmas to make a Jew feel like a
minority,'' observes Glicksman. Although she is not religious, she
bridles when she sees ``Hanukkah bushes'' or Jewish friends
exchange Christmas gifts. And even people who know she is Jewish
send her Christmas cards with religious images. ``Sure, it's the
thought that counts, but a little more thinking could have gone a
long way,'' she writes.
</P>
<P>
   (slugged: BC-HANUKKAH-BUSH-HUMBUG-(HOLIDAYS)-ART-NYTSF, priority
code r, category code l)
</P>
<P>
   For purchase information and to obtain photos, call New York
