<HEADLINE>
FRENCH RIGHTIST CHIEF OUSTS DEPUTY
</HEADLINE>
  (bl) 
 By CRAIG R. WHITNEY    
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   PARIS _ The leader of France's extreme-right National Front
Party, Jean-Marie Le Pen, on Wednesday dismissed his longtime
deputy, Bruno Megret for openly challenging his leadership. Megret
called for an extraordinary party congress next month after
disagreeing on tactics and strategy with Le Pen, the party's
founder.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-09-98 2128EST &QL; 
