<P>
   (NYT11) UNDATED -- Dec. 9, 1998 -- HOME-IMPROVEMENT-B&AMP;W, 12-09
-- During the fall, homeowners often awaken to find their windows
fogged over. In the winter, the windows may be covered with a thin
layer of frost. Both the fog and the frost are examples of
condensation. Moderate condensation is not a cause for concern.
Heavy persistent condensation will flow past the sill to saturate
the wall. Damp walls will encourage mold and mildew. Eventually the
moisture will penetrate through the walls and rot the framing. (New
York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
