years ago, developers were outbidding one another for the old
office towers to turn into new apartment buildings. While no one is
labeling the Wall Street experiment in living a bust, the pace has
definitely slowed. (Suzanne DeChillo/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT9) NEW YORK -- Dec. 9, 1998 -- NY-WINTER-GARDEN, 12-09 -- A
visitor looks at a sculptured hedge in the winter solstice garden
at the New York Botanical Garden in the Bronx. Workers with
Fernleigh Productions are displaying their work in New York at the
invitation of the garden's director, Gregory Long. Planning for the
exhibit began in January. (Suzanne DeChillo/New York Times Photo)
</P>
