<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CLAIBORNE NAMED ALL-AMERICAN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC linebacker Chris Claiborne continued to add to
his lists of honors Wednesday by making the American Football
Coaches Association All-American team.
</P>
<P>
   The honor keeps Claiborne on pace to be USC's first unanimous
All-American. The last Trojan to become a consensus All-American
was wide receiver Keyshawn Johnson in 1995.
</P>
<P>
   Claiborne has two more All-American teams to make before
officially becoming a unanimous All-American.
</P>
<P>
   Claiborne will attend USC's team banquet tonight, then take a
red-eye flight to Orlando for Friday's Butkus Award presentation.
</P>
<P>
   Hawaii update: Defensive coordinator Bill Young's chances for
the University of Hawaii job improved Wednesday, after Utah coach
Ron McBride pulled out of the running.
</P>
<P>
   That leaves Young, San Diego Chargers interim coach June Jones
and Arizona assistant Duane Akina as the top candidates for the
job.
</P>
<P>
   Hawaii interviewed Jones, who is currently considered the
leading candidate, on Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
   Young has been told he would hear from Hawaii by the weekend.
</P>
<P>
   Practice canceled: With academics causing about 15 players to
miss practice, USC decided to cancel Wednesday's session. The
Trojans will be off until Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   The rest will be good for wide receiver R. Jay Soward, who
tweaked his ankle in last weekend's practice but will return
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Defensive tackle Aaron Williams has been bothered by a strained
Achilles' tendon but is expected to return to practice before the
Sun Bowl. Florida State fan: USC tailback Chad Morton is confident
that No. 2-ranked Florida State will defeat No. 1-ranked Tennessee
in the Fiesta Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   He's believed the Seminoles were the nation's top team since the
Trojans lost, 30-10, in Tallahassee in September.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm going to stick to that pick until the season is over,''
Morton said. ``I always thought they should be at the top.''
</P>
<P>
   Morton is also lamenting that the Trojans ground game was not
nearly as successful as Miami tailback Edgerrin James, who rushed
for 299 yards against the Bruins.
</P>
<P>
   ``We felt that if we had more chances to run the ball, we would
have done better, but we had to start playing catchup right away,''
Morton said.
</P>
<P>
   New awards: USC will hold its football banquet tonight, and
coach Paul Hackett has added three awards _ linemen of the year,
top scout team players and special teams player of the year.
</P>
<P>
   TC-who?: Hackett was still a little unsure about Sun Bowl
opponent Texas Christian, because USC had not received game film
until late Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know anything about them except they're a good running
team,'' Hackett said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
