<SLUG> BC-FBC-UCLA-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
UCLA HANDS OUT FOOTBALL HONORS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Several area athletes were honored Wednesday at
UCLA's postseason banquet at the Beverly Hilton Hotel.
</P>
<P>
   Senior center Shawn Stuart, from Saugus, won for all-around
excellence (the Paul Wellman Memorial) and academic achievement
(Jack R. Robinson Award).
</P>
<P>
   Tight end Gabe Crecion, of Northridge, was honored for
outstanding performance by a scout team player (Charles Pike
Memorial).
</P>
<P>
   And tailback Mark Reynosa, of Sylmar, received the Terry Donahue
Award for achievement by a walk-on.
</P>
<P>
   Among the other honorees were quarterback Cade McNown and safety
Larry Atkins, who shared the Red Sanders Award for most valuable
player.
</P>
<P>
   Injury update: Starting nose guard Micah Webb has a torn medial
collateral ligament in his left knee and will not play in the Rose
Bowl. Freshman Ken Kocher probably will start in Webb's place.
</P>
<P>
   Wait and see: Coach Bob Toledo returned from a recruiting trip
Wednesday and said he'll evaluate the future of beleaguered
defensive coordinator Nick Aliotti after the Rose Bowl _ as he
usually does with his assistants.
</P>
<P>
   ``When the season's over, we'll discuss it,'' Toledo said. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
